@page "/rules"

<PageTitle>Magic Draft Stats - Rules</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-2 mt-md-4">
    <h1><i class="bi bi-journal-text me-4 d-none d-md-inline"></i>Rules</h1>
    <p class="lead mt-4">These are some rules clarifications that we've encountered when playing with our Magic Foundations cube.</p>
    
    <div class="card mt-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">
                Valkyrie's Call and Witness Protection
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center gap-4 flex-wrap mb-3">
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/27/valkyries-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Valkyries%20Call&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Valkyrie's Call" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/185/llanowar-elves" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Llanowar%20Elves&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Llanowar Elves" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/168/witness-protection" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Witness%20Protection&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Witness Protection" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4">
                <span class="fs-5">
                    I have <strong>Valkyrie's Call</strong> in play, as well as a <strong>Llanowar Elves</strong> that has already died and come back as an Angel with a +1/+1 counter on it. My opponent then plays <strong>Witness Protection</strong> on it. It is now a base 1/1 Citizen with a +1/+1 counter on it (making it a 2/2), but it is no longer an Angel and does not have flying. If it dies again, Valkyrie's Call will trigger and return it as a new Angel with a +1/+1 counter on it once more.
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="card mt-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">
                Valkyrie's Call and Nine-Lives Familiar
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center gap-4 flex-wrap mb-3">
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/27/valkyries-call" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Valkyries%20Call&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Valkyrie's Call" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/66/nine-lives-familiar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Nine-Lives%20Familiar&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Nine-Lives Familiar" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4">
                <span class="fs-5">
                    If <strong>Nine-Lives Familiar</strong> dies while <strong>Valkyrie's Call</strong> is in play, it returns as a flying Angel with no revival counters (since it wasn't <em>cast</em>). This trigger is not optional, and the delayed trigger from <strong>Nine-Lives Familiar</strong> itself will do nothing at the next end step.
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card mt-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">
                Giada, Font of Hope and Taurean Mauler
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center gap-4 flex-wrap mb-3">
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/14/giada-font-of-hope" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Giada%2C%20Font%20of%20Hope&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Giada, Font of Hope" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/155/taurean-mauler" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Taurean%20Mauler&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Taurean Mauler" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4">
                <span class="fs-5">
                    <strong>Taurean Mauler</strong> is a Changeling, which means it has every creature type — including Angel. If <strong>Giada, Font of Hope</strong> is in play, Taurean Mauler will enter the battlefield with an additional +1/+1 counter on it. Changeling is a "characteristic-defining ability", which is active in all zones.
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card mt-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">
                Think Twice and Scavenging Ooze
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center gap-4 flex-wrap mb-3">
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/74/think-twice" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Think%20Twice&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Think Twice" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
                <a href="https://scryfall.com/card/fdn/189/scavenging-ooze" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <img src="https://api.scryfall.com/cards/named?exact=Scavenging%20Ooze&set=fdn&format=image" alt="Scavenging Ooze" class="img-fluid rounded-3 shadow" style="max-width: 320px;" />
                </a>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4">
                <span class="fs-5">
                    If <strong>Think Twice</strong> is in an opponent's graveyard, you can activate <strong>Scavenging Ooze</strong>'s ability targeting it. In response, your opponent can Flashback <strong>Think Twice</strong>. When <strong>Scavenging Ooze</strong>'s ability tries to resolve, <strong>Think Twice</strong> is no longer in the graveyard (it was exiled as part of Flashback), so the ability does nothing — no card is exiled, no +1/+1 counter is placed, and no life is gained.
                </span>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
                <span class="fs-5">
                    If the opponent casts <strong>Think Twice</strong> using Flashback from their graveyard, it will be put on the stack, and by the time players get priority, it will no longer be in the graveyard, so <strong>Scavenging Ooze</strong>'s ability will not be able to target it at all.
                </span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center text-muted small mt-5 mb-2">
        Card images courtesy of <a href="https://scryfall.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scryfall</a>
    </div>
</div> 